On March 10, 2014, President Barack Obama issued a sequestration order for fiscal year 2015. This order stated that on October 1, 2014, direct spending budgetary resources for fiscal year 2015 in each non-exempt budget account should be reduced by the amount calculated by the Office of Management and Budget. The sequestrations were to be made in accordance with the requirements of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act and the specifications of the Office of Management and Budget's report.